n the first or second layers. The least one second via has a depth dimension that is less than a depth dimension of the first via. A metallic trace (70, 72) is applied between the exposed area on the mechanical layer and a portion of the second via. The wafer is sliced such that the second via is separated into two sections, thereby creating a sensor die. The sensor die is then electrically and mechanically bonded to a circuit board at the sliced second via.
